paragraphs.title: preprocessing functions - make AWS DF (홍성죽도)
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import DoubleType
from pyspark.sql.types import IntegerType
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

udf_floatize = udf(lambda s: float(s), DoubleType())
udf_dt2dh = udf(lambda dhm: dhm[:13])

sun = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///ds/sun.parquet').collect()
awsdf_col = ['date_hm', 'temp', '1mRainfall', 'rainOrNot', 'wind', 'windVelo', 'humid']

def is_number(s):
    try:
        float(s)
        return True
    except ValueError:
        return False

def getsrs(day):
    rs = list(filter(lambda s: s[0] == day, sun))
    return {'rise': rs[0][1],
            'set': rs[0][2]}

def reformatAWSDF(df):
    oldcolnames = df.schema.names
    header = df.first()
    
    # remove unnecessary row col
    df = df.filter('%s != "%s"' % (oldcolnames[0], header[0]))\
           .drop(oldcolnames[0], oldcolnames[7], oldcolnames[8], 
                 oldcolnames[10], oldcolnames[11])
    del oldcolnames[0]
    del oldcolnames[6]
    del oldcolnames[6]
    del oldcolnames[7]
    del oldcolnames[7]
    
    # remove null
    for colname in oldcolnames:
        df = df.filter('%s is not null' % colname)
    
    # df.show()

    # change column name new
    for idx in range(len(awsdf_col)):
        if idx == 0:
            df = df.withColumnRenamed(oldcolnames[idx], awsdf_col[idx])
        else:
            df = df.withColumn(awsdf_col[idx], udf_floatize(oldcolnames[idx]))
            
    # select available columns
    df = df.select('date_hm', 'temp', '1mRainfall', 'rainOrNot',
                   'wind', 'windVelo', 'humid')
    return df
    
def getmerge_awsdf(filelist_hdfs):
    # read dfs from hdfs
    dfs = []
    for i in range(12):
        dfs.append(spark.read.csv('hdfs:///raw/kma_aws/%d.csv' % (i+1)))
        dfs[i] = reformatAWSDF(dfs[i])

    # merge dfs
    merged_df = dfs[0].union(dfs[1])
    for i in range(9):
        merged_df = merged_df.union(dfs[i+2])

    # make column of datehour
    merged_df = merged_df.withColumn('datehour', udf_dt2dh(df.date_hm))\
                         .drop('date_hm')
       
    # group by hour and avg
    merged_df = merged_df.groupBy('datehour')\
                         .avg('temp', 'humid', 'wind', 'windVelo')\
                         .sort('datehour')
    
    return merged_df

def showCorrMtx(df):
    pdf = df.toPandas()
    corr = pdf.corr()
    mask = np.zeros_like(corr)
    mask[np.triu_indices_from(mask)] = True
    ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(11,11))
    ax = sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, mask=mask,
                     cmap="YlGnBu")

paragraphs.title: preprocessing - kma Anmyeondo uv
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.sql import Row

locationcode = 132

awsdata_filelist_hdfs = []
for i in range(12):
        awsdata_filelist_hdfs.append('hdfs:///raw/kma_aws/%d.csv' % (i+1))

uva = sc.textFile('hdfs:///raw/kma_uva_2017')\
        .filter(lambda s: s != 'Site: Anmyeon')\
        .map(lambda s: s.split(','))\
        .filter(lambda s: is_number(s[1].strip()))\
        .map(lambda s: [s[0][:4] + '-' + s[0][4:6] + '-' + s[0][6:8],
                        s[0][8:],
                        float(s[1].strip()),
                        float(s[2].strip())])\
        .map(lambda s: Row(datehour=s[0]+ ' ' + s[1], sum_uva=s[2], max_uva=s[3]))\
        .toDF()

uvb = sc.textFile('hdfs:///raw/kma_uvb_2017')\
        .filter(lambda s: s != 'Site: Anmyeon')\
        .map(lambda s: s.split(','))\
        .filter(lambda s: is_number(s[1].strip()))\
        .map(lambda s: [s[0][:4] + '-' + s[0][4:6] + '-' + s[0][6:8],
                        s[0][8:],
                        float(s[1].strip()),
                        float(s[2].strip())])\
        .map(lambda s: Row(datehour=s[0]+ ' ' + s[1], sum_uvb=s[2], max_uvb=s[3]))\
        .toDF()
        
uva.write.mode("overwrite")\
         .parquet("hdfs:///ds/kma_uva.parquet")
uvb.write.mode("overwrite")\
         .parquet("hdfs:///ds/kma_uvb.parquet")

uva.show()
uvb.show()

# join
df_awsuv = df.join(uva, 'datehour')\
             .join(uvb, 'datehour')
# df_awsuv.show()
df_awsuv.createOrReplaceTempView('aws_uv')

paragraphs.title: add new column
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

udf_dh2date = udf(lambda dh: dh.split(' ')[0])
udf_dh2hour = udf(lambda dh: int(dh.split(' ')[1]), IntegerType())
udf_dh2month = udf(lambda dh: int(dh.split('-')[1]), IntegerType())

df_awsuv_s = df_awsuv.sort('datehour')\
                     .withColumn('date', udf_dh2date(df_awsuv.datehour))\
                     .withColumn('hour', udf_dh2hour(df_awsuv.datehour))\
                     .withColumn('month', udf_dh2month(df_awsuv.datehour))\
                     .drop('datehour')

df_awsuv_s.printSchema()
df_awsuv_s.show()

%pyspark
df_awsuv_spring = df_awsuv_s.where('month >= 3 and month <= 5')\
                            .drop('month', 'hour')
df_awsuv_summer = df_awsuv_s.where('month >= 6 and month <= 8')\
                            .drop('month', 'hour')
df_awsuv_fall = df_awsuv_s.where('month >= 9 and month <= 11')\
                          .drop('month', 'hour')
df_awsuv_winter = df_awsuv_s.where('month >= 12 or month <= 2')\
                            .drop('month', 'hour')
